            <p><a href="https://github.com/cferdinandi/smooth-scroll">GitHub</a>, <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/smooth-scroll">npm</a>
            </p>
            <p>A lightweight script to animate scrolling to anchor links. This provides a better user experience for navigating one-page sites or long landing pages.</p>
            <p>Leap automatically applies the animation effect to all links with the <code>data-smooth-scroll</code> attribute.</p>
            <p>You may have a nav which obscures the focussed element after it is scrolled to the top of the window. To avoid this, add the <code>data-smooth-scroll-offset="110"</code> where <code>110</code> is a value in pixels which matches the height
              of your nav.</p>

          </div>
        </article>

